        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 10:52AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1051 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Rutherford, or 12 miles north of Trenton, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sandhill, Kenton, Dyer, Sidonia, Dresden, Bradford, Good Luck,
Kimery, Sharon, Greenfield, Rutherford, Skullbone, Crowley Store,
Currie, Big Cypress Tree State Park, Staffords Store, Pillowville,
Tilghman, Barrons Corner, and Tyson Store.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
